headlines.description: — Coby White scored 35 points, Nikola Vucevic added 22 points and 12 rebounds and the Chicago Bulls outlasted Charlotte 117-110 on Wednesday night to send the Hornets to their fifth straight loss.
headlines.shortLinkText: Coby White scores 35 points to help Bulls hand Hornets their fifth straight loss 117-110

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 20 of his 45 points in the fourth quarter, Darius Garland had 19 points in his return from a broken jaw and the Cleveland Cavaliers held off the NBA-worst Detroit Pistons 128-121 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Donovan Mitchell scores 45 points, Cavs hold off Pistons 128-121 in Darius Garland's return

headlines.description: — Kawhi Leonard scored 31 points, James Harden added 25 and the Los Angeles Clippers pulled away with a big third quarter to beat the Washington Wizards 125-109 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Leonard, Harden help Clippers pull away from Wizards, 125-109

headlines.description: — Jimmy Butler scored 31 points and the Miami Heat snapped a seven-game skid with a 115-106 victory over the Sacramento Kings on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Butler scores 31 points to help Heat beat Kings 115-106 and snap 7-game skid

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Houston Rockets

headlines.description: — Jonas Valanciunas scored 25 points, Brandon Ingram added 24 and the duo combined for 24 rebounds to help the New Orleans Pelicans snap a three-game skid with a 110-99 win over the Houston Rockets on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Valanciunas and Ingram lead Pelicans past Rockets 110-99 to snap 3-game skid

headlines.description: — Karl-Anthony Towns had 29 points and nine rebounds for the Minnesota Timberwolves in a 121-87 victory over the depleted Dallas...
headlines.shortLinkText: Towns leads Timberwolves in 121-87 win over Mavs team missing Doncic and Irving

events.name: Orlando Magic at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Paolo Banchero scored 25 points, Franz Wagner added 20 and the Orlando Magic held on to beat the San Antonio Spurs 108-98 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Magic stave off fourth-quarter rally and topple Spurs 108-98

events.name: Denver Nuggets at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 34 points to help the Oklahoma City Thunder beat the short-handed Denver Nuggets 105-100 on Wednesday night in a matchup of teams near the top of the Western Conference standings.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander scores 34 points, Thunder beat short-handed Nuggets 105-100

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant was cheered before the game, then booed when it started.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kevin Durant scores 33 points in Brooklyn return, leads Suns to 136-120 victory over the Nets

events.name: Milwaukee Bucks at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Damian Lillard's former team took a bit of the shine off his gala homecoming.
headlines.shortLinkText: Trail Blazers spoil Lillard's return to Portland with a 119-116 victory over Bucks
